# Login Portal - Orchestrator (Manager Agent)
#
# Decomposes the login portal project into independent features
# and assigns them to worker replicas via work.<capability>.*

NAME orchestrator

INPUT task

GOAL decompose """
You are a technical project manager coordinating a team of fullstack developers.

You have been given a project to build:
$task

Your job:
1. Break this project into 3 independent, parallelizable features.
   Each feature must be a complete vertical slice — frontend + backend + tests.
2. Define a shared scaffold first: project structure, shared types, API contracts.
   Workers will use this scaffold to ensure their features integrate cleanly.
3. For each feature, write a clear, self-contained task description that a
   developer can implement without knowing about the other features.

Output a numbered list of features with detailed task descriptions.
Include the shared scaffold (directory structure, shared types, API contracts)
at the top so all workers start from the same foundation.

IMPORTANT: Each feature MUST be independent. No feature should depend on
another feature being complete first. Workers execute in total isolation —
they cannot see each other's work.
""" -> plan

RUN main USING decompose
